00:51:45.660 --> 00:51:47.550
of how much denim
you wore as a kid.

00:51:47.550 --> 00:51:50.050
I mean, that's-- wow.

00:51:50.050 --> 00:51:53.430
And it was like the one time
as a kid his family went down

00:51:53.430 --> 00:51:55.740
to London, happened
to be photographed

00:51:55.740 --> 00:51:59.370
by a distant relative of the
person he would go on to marry.

00:51:59.370 --> 00:52:01.475
And then it was
the one photograph

00:52:01.475 --> 00:52:02.850
that they wanted
to show you when

00:52:02.850 --> 00:52:04.440
you happened to
visit in this other--

00:52:04.440 --> 00:52:05.775
it's just insane, right?

00:52:05.775 --> 00:52:07.650
And again, they showed
this at their wedding,

00:52:07.650 --> 00:52:11.903
about how incredible it was
that they had this photo.

00:52:11.903 --> 00:52:12.570
And that's true.

00:52:12.570 --> 00:52:13.830
It is incredible for them.

00:52:13.830 --> 00:52:15.240
It's just not incredible
that it happens.

00:52:15.240 --> 00:52:17.823
Always, you just got to remember
how many opportunities things

00:52:17.823 --> 00:52:19.020
have to happen.

00:52:19.020 --> 00:52:21.920
In fact, you can
kind of exploit that.

00:52:21.920 --> 00:52:25.470
So I've got a-- this is an
old-school one-pound coin,

00:52:25.470 --> 00:52:27.970
the old circular ones,
before they got rid of them.

00:52:27.970 --> 00:52:31.050
I'm going to flip it so it
lands on its edge, right?

00:52:31.050 --> 00:52:35.010
So flip the coin,
land, edge, OK?

00:52:35.010 --> 00:52:35.640
OK, here we go.

00:52:35.640 --> 00:52:35.930
Ready?

00:52:35.930 --> 00:52:36.430
Ready?

00:52:40.230 --> 00:52:41.340
That's dangerously close.

00:52:47.749 --> 00:52:49.870
Oh!

00:52:49.870 --> 00:52:50.890
That's so close.

00:52:50.890 --> 00:52:52.300
Wouldn't that have been amazing?

00:52:52.300 --> 00:52:53.870
I mean, I thought I was just
going to have to stand here,

00:52:53.870 --> 00:52:56.560
doing the same thing over
and over again, but no.

00:52:56.560 --> 00:52:57.850
No, actually, that was--

00:52:57.850 --> 00:53:00.130
the pound coin, I think,
is the most likely thing

00:53:00.130 --> 00:53:00.970
to land on its edge.

00:53:00.970 --> 00:53:02.290
And just so you know,
that doesn't always

00:53:02.290 --> 00:53:03.230
happen, by the way.

00:53:03.230 --> 00:53:04.150
There's not an edge.

00:53:04.150 --> 00:53:06.250
I happened to get lucky
on the first flip, right?

00:53:06.250 --> 00:53:07.840
It genuinely does happen.

00:53:07.840 --> 00:53:11.560
I could actually-- I could sit
here for-- ooh, that was close.

00:53:11.560 --> 00:53:14.020
I could sit here and flip
it thousands of times.

00:53:14.020 --> 00:53:17.860
Eventually, it would land
on its edge, which I know,

00:53:17.860 --> 00:53:19.660
because I did.

00:53:19.660 --> 00:53:24.400
So this was me flipping a coin
until it lands on its edge.

00:53:24.400 --> 00:53:26.910
I wanted to see how
many edges I could get.

00:53:26.910 --> 00:53:29.410
And some of them, I wasn't sure
if they should count or not.

00:53:29.410 --> 00:53:31.000
So I want your
opinion on this one.

00:53:31.000 --> 00:53:31.625
OK, here we go.

00:53:31.625 --> 00:53:35.177
This is me flipping a coin
so it lands on its edge.

00:53:35.177 --> 00:53:38.590
Flip the coin.

00:53:38.590 --> 00:53:40.660
Look at that!

00:53:40.660 --> 00:53:43.622
Wait, wait.

00:53:43.622 --> 00:53:46.510
Oh no.

00:53:46.510 --> 00:53:47.500
No, no, no, no, no, no.

00:53:47.500 --> 00:53:49.160
Aw.

00:53:49.160 --> 00:53:50.610
Does that count?

00:53:50.610 --> 00:53:53.180
Vote if you think that counts.

00:53:53.180 --> 00:53:54.760
Vote if you think it doesn't.

00:53:54.760 --> 00:53:55.430
You're right.

00:53:55.430 --> 00:53:57.140
It does not.

00:53:57.140 --> 00:53:57.920
I kept going.

00:53:57.920 --> 00:54:04.820
I flipped this specific
coin 10,000 times.

00:54:04.820 --> 00:54:06.430
Oh, I haven't put
the video out yet.

00:54:06.430 --> 00:54:08.142
So people watching
this, spoiler.

00:54:08.142 --> 00:54:09.100
Don't tell anyone else.

00:54:09.100 --> 00:54:10.330
That video will be out soon.

00:54:10.330 --> 00:54:12.430
I flipped it-- because I did,
like, funny videos like, here's

00:54:12.430 --> 00:54:14.347
how you flip a coin till
it lands on its edge.

00:54:14.347 --> 00:54:15.840
Boom, thanks, right?

00:54:15.840 --> 00:54:16.958
There's a video.

00:54:16.958 --> 00:54:18.250
And I kept going, going, going.

00:54:18.250 --> 00:54:21.880
14-- 14 edges out
of 10,000 flips.

00:54:21.880 --> 00:54:26.560
I believe the old circular
pound coin is the most likely to

00:54:26.560 --> 00:54:28.180
land on its edge
of all the coins.

00:54:28.180 --> 00:54:29.800
That's my theory.

00:54:29.800 --> 00:54:31.180
And it seems pretty likely.

00:54:31.180 --> 00:54:35.690
I couldn't believe I
almost got an edge just--

00:54:35.690 --> 00:54:37.030
aw.

00:54:37.030 --> 00:54:37.550
Right?

00:54:37.550 --> 00:54:40.370
And so if you ever want
to pass, in my experience,

00:54:40.370 --> 00:54:44.150
three days of your
life, get involved.

00:54:44.150 --> 00:54:51.050
OK, so I think we've done enough
ridiculous bits of probability.

00:54:51.050 --> 00:54:54.290
We'll go back to the show
as I originally planned.

00:54:54.290 --> 00:54:58.670
Oh, and to be honest,
I am quite glad.

00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:02.090
It's great example
of probability.

00:55:02.090 --> 00:55:03.650
If you do something
often enough,

00:55:03.650 --> 00:55:04.692
weird things will happen.

00:55:04.692 --> 00:55:07.067
I like the fact that we got
three probabilities in a row.

00:55:07.067 --> 00:55:08.810
I think that's
actually quite a good--

00:55:08.810 --> 00:55:11.450
quite a good message,
although the bizarre thing

00:55:11.450 --> 00:55:14.000
is, this is the first
time I have ever done

00:55:14.000 --> 00:55:14.810
this talk, right?

00:55:14.810 --> 00:55:17.280
And it happened straight away.

00:55:17.280 --> 00:55:19.100
And for those of you
watching the video,

00:55:19.100 --> 00:55:20.630
it's because we
sat here and kept

00:55:20.630 --> 00:55:23.725
spinning it until we got
probability every single time.

00:55:23.725 --> 00:55:25.100
This is the most
patient audience

00:55:25.100 --> 00:55:26.990
I've had for some time.

00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:29.360
And this is a lesson
in not believing

00:55:29.360 --> 00:55:31.610
things you see on the internet.

00:55:31.610 --> 00:55:34.015
So good moral.

